recordedBy: L. Smith, A. Magnanini, G. Machline, L. S. Silva, W. T. Ormond & J. Augusto
locality: Distrito Federal, Praia de Grumari, próximo à Guaratiba.

occurrenceRemarks: Internodes semiglossy, gray-green, 3-4 cm long, 2.5 cm diam.; cataphylls drying dark brown, more or less intact; petioles terete, weakly and narrowly sulcate, semiglossy dark green; blades moderately coriaceous, glossy, weakly bicolorous; midrib bluntly acute to convex and concolorous above, narrow-raised and paler below; primary lateral veins flat to weakly sulcate above, convex below; tertiary veins obscure; spathe green, spreading, margins underrolled; spadix dark purple, matte; tepals upturned against pistils. Cultivated by Dewey Fisk. Originally from Brazil. Cultivated Plant. Missouri Botanical Garden Herbarium (MO). Sheet 1 of 2. See also CAS 1074191, barcode 599814. Additional collecting information and specimen description listed on Tropicos specimen search.
